tic orbit around the sun or if you have other large bodies close enough to affect you.<\/p>\n","answer_id":13503,"question_id":13502,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1384573903}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/13502/what-significance-is-the-moon","last_activity_date":1384573903,"creation_date":1384521823,"answer_count":1,"title":"what significance is the moon?","body":"<p>Why is it that planets like Mercury, Venus and Pluto do not have moons? or how significant is a planet having even one moon? How does it affect the planet's ecosystem, especially seasons and periods?\nthanks<\/p>\n","question_id":13502,"tags":["ecosystem"],"score":-5,"down_vote_count":6,"closed_reason":"off-topic","is_answered":true,"view_count":342,"up_vote_count":1},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/f0PGT.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3615,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3615/biogirl","reputation":3923,"display_name":"biogirl","accept_rate":89},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4f8a4da7480c620ebaa9ed7c31fb227b?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4840,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4840/a-kennard","reputation":1429,"display_name":"A. Kennard"},"score":1,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/f0PGT.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3615,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3615/biogirl","reputation":3923,"display_name":"biogirl","accept_rate":89},"score":0,"post_id":13512,"edited":false,"creation_date":1384537541,"comment_id":17519,"body":"I agree with @Alan Boyd. Even I do not understand why 1kb should be there ?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4f8a4da7480c620ebaa9ed7c31fb227b?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4840,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4840/a-kennard","reputation":1429,"display_name":"A. Kenn