in - HCl secreted by parietal cells of the gastric glands acidifies the stomach) the protein is able to cleave off its own propeptide, making it fully active.<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/tx3xF.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/p>\n","answer_id":13481,"question_id":13479,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1384445980}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/13479/energetics-and-products-of-pepsin-hcl-protein-digestion","last_activity_date":1384445980,"creation_date":1384416285,"answer_count":1,"title":"Energetics and Products of Pepsin/HCl Protein Digestion","body":"<p>What are the energetics of protein digestion during which the enzyme pepsin is \"activated\" (whatever that means) by HCl?  I've looked and been unable to find anything like a chemical equation that includes an energy term.<\/p>\n\n<p>Of course, pepsin, being an enzyme, is not used up in that sought-for equation.  Is HCl used up?  If so, what are the products?  How and in what form is the chlorine removed, assuming the HCl is consumed in the equation?<\/p>\n","question_id":13479,"tags":["digestive-system"],"score":2,"accepted_answer_id":13481,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":522,"up_vote_count":2},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/113cbd78d7b98635d06c25f31f0b2b94?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4104,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4104/donkey-2009","reputation":148,"display_name":"Donkey_2009"},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/GqkqP.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4101,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4101/amory","reputation":7383,"display_name":"Amory"},"score":11,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/113cbd78d7b98635d06c25f31f0b2b94?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4104,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4104/donkey-2009","r