},"score":2,"is_accepted":false,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date":1384180521,"creation_date":1384180521,"body":"<p>First of all, the 4.4 kb HindIII band is derived from the right end of &lambda; DNA, so during storage it anneals to the 23.1 kb left arm fragment via &lambda;'s 12 bp cohesive ends. You can solve this problem by preheating the markers to 65&deg;C for a few minutes then cooling rapidly (i.e. on ice). <\/p>\n\n<p>In a stained gel the intensity of a band is proportional to the amount of DNA in that band. This is why the heavier bands are more intense. The fragment X in lane 2 is similar in intensity to the 0.5 kb &lambda; fragment so DNA content of the two bands is similar.<\/p>\n\n<p>The amount of DNA in the 0.5 kb band is 250 ng *(0.5/48.5) where 48.5 is the size of wild-type &lambda; DNA. I'll leave it for you to complete the calculation.<\/p>\n","answer_id":13428,"question_id":13418,"up_vote_count":2}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/13418/why-is-the-4-4-kb-band-barely-visible-in-this-hindiii-digest-of-lambda-dna","last_activity_date":1384180559,"creation_date":1384122867,"answer_count":1,"title":"Why is the 4.4 kb band barely visible in this HindIII digest of lambda DNA?","body":"<p>Why is the 4.4 kb band barely visible? <\/p>\n\n<p>Also, what is the mass (ng) of DNA in band X if lane S contains 250 ng of digested lambda phage DNA?<\/p>\n\n<p><img src=\"http://i.stack.imgur.com/JLXfe.jpg\" alt=\"enter image description here\"><\/p>\n","question_id":13418,"tags":["genetics"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":1,"is_answered":true,"view_count":247,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1384180559},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b76e4c5e6ced288c175c5f66f777f97c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4897,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4897/thegoerge","reputation":11,"display_name":"thegoerge"},"closed_date":1384436396,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/13427/gliotoxin-ingestion-and-actions-needed","last_activity_date":1384175812,"creation_date":1384175812,"answer_count":0,"title":"Gliotoxin ingestion and actions needed","body":"<p>what are the \"next day\" actions that one has to take, when accidentally ingests contaminated drink/food from Aspergillus or Penicillium or Candida fungus?<\/p>\n\n<p>Is it feasible to take N-acetyl-L-cysteine supplements? What other measures minimize the damage from the mycotoxins?<\/p>\n\n<p>What kind of supplements and/or treatments reduce the superoxides produced as effect of the mycotoxins?<\/p>\n","question_id":13427,"tags":["toxicology","mycology"],"score":2,"down_vote_count":0,"closed_reason":"off-topic","is_answered":false,"view_count":18,"up_vote_count":2},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/96d1c1db6522a2c7a8a3548da98c0a56?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":4889,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4889/meeyu","reputation":11,"display_name":"meeyu"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1MUb2.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1306,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1306/terdon","reputation":9339,"display_name":"terdon","accept_rate":73},"score":0,"post_id":13412,"edited":false,"creation_date":1384097152,"comment_id":17358,"body":"In vacuum for example?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/96d1c1db6522a2c7a8a3548da98c0a56?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"unregistered","user_id":4889,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4889/meeyu","reputation":11,"display_name":"meeyu"},"score":0,"post_id":13412,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1MUb2.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1306,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1306/terdon","reputation":9339,"display_name":"terdon","accept_rate":73},"edited":false,"creation_date":1384097833,"comment_id":17359,"body":"In vacuum, exactly."}],"answers