e to differences in specific details such as the vehicle, dilution scheme and laboratory protocols for various mouse LD50 assays, units of biological activity of MYOBLOC (botulinum toxin type b) cannot be compared to or converted into units of any other botulinum toxin or any toxin assessed with any other specific assay method. Therefore, differences in species sensitivities to different botulinum neurotoxin serotypes preclude extrapolation of animal dose-activity relationships to human dose estimates. The specific activity of MYOBLOC (botulinum toxin type b) ranges between 70 to 130 Units/ng.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<p>UPDATE<\/p>\n\n<p>10 pg of <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Botulinum_toxin\" rel=\"nofollow\">toxin<\/a> (150 kDa) is 4 x 10<sup>9<\/sup> molecules<\/p>\n","answer_id":12404,"question_id":11397,"up_vote_count":5,"last_edit_date":1384020820}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/11397/what-is-one-botulinum-toxin-medical-unit","last_activity_date":1384093603,"creation_date":1383988548,"answer_count":1,"title":"What is one Botulinum toxin medical unit?","body":"<p>How many Botulinum toxin molecules or grams are contained in one medical unit of Botox?<\/p>\n","question_id":11397,"tags":["bacterial-toxins","dose"],"score":2,"accepted_answer_id":12404,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":141,"up_vote_count":2,"last_edit_date":1384093603},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0f253ddf975dde9df19c7cd3fc8a739e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":4884,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4884/jb510","reputation":133,"display_name":"jb510"},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/533dbaaadd30c65ab484e999e61e35c6?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":4882,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/4882/sg324","reputation":56,"display_name":"SG324"},"score":4,"is_accepted":true,"down_vote_count":0,"last_activity_date